OCEAN PRINT GIVEAWAY! 🎉 

It’s round two of our #OceanMonth and we’re thrilled to announce a print giveaway with ocean & surf photographer @nickpumphreyphoto ! 

Reconnect with the wonders of #PlanetOcean through his lens and let the breathtaking imagery transport you to a place of serenity and peace.

To participate, follow these simple steps:

1️⃣ Follow @FairPlanet_ and @nickpumphreyphoto and tag a friend in the comments!

2️⃣ Share this post in your story to double your chance of winning :)

🏆 One lucky winner will be chosen at random to receive a hand-signed photo print by Nick. Don't miss out on this opportunity to bring the tranquility of the sea into your home! 

📅 Giveaway ends June 20th at 00:00 CEST and the winner will be raffled on the 21st! Open to participants worldwide. Good luck to all of you! 🤞
_____________

Over the week, we will be talking about a key aspect of his work: reconnection - and what it has to do with solutions to protect the ocean! Stay tuned 🙌

#ReconnectToProtect

Connect to Protect 🌊

Hear @nickpumphreyphoto ‘s powerful message for ocean solutions!

Featuring captivating shots from @gregwdennis “Be there Be present,” captured during the Covid pandemic, this film emphasizes the vital importance of rediscovering our connection to nature in order to tackle the most pressing issues of today! 💪🏼

What’s your favorite ocean solution? Explore more on FairPlanet.org. 🌍

______

And don’t miss your chance to connect with the ocean from the comfort of your home! 

You can still win a hand-signed A2-sized print of Nick’s marvellous ocean photography. 

To join our giveaway until the 20th of June:

Like and comment on one of the posts we created with Nick (including this) and follow FairPlanet to sign up! 

Good luck 🤞🏼

The new issue of @wavelengthsurfmag is out and it’s a beauty, the theme is ‘Connection’ and couldn’t be more fitting when it comes to wave riding and creativity. Thank you @laymike and @tobybutlerphoto for your stellar work and including some of my photography. Here is one of my photos from an article with @jacobdown_ , a year of work together and an intricate insight by him into the iconic @campbellbros Bonzer surfboard design and the experiences felt along the way. You can grab a copy through the link in their bio. 🌊
